			ctx = templ.InitializeContext(ctx)
			templ_7745c5c3_Err = templruntime.WriteString(templ_7745c5c3_Buffer, 4, "<div class=\"guide guide-content\"><a href=\"/guide\" class=\"back-link\">&larr; Back to Guide</a><h1>Recommended Pokemon</h1><p>These are reliable, easy-to-find Pokemon that can carry you through the game. You do not need all of them &mdash; just pick a few that cover your team's weaknesses.</p><h2>FireRed / LeafGreen</h2><h3>Gyarados</h3><p><strong>Type:</strong> Water/Flying &mdash; <strong>Where:</strong> Buy Magikarp ($500) at Route 4 Pokemon Center (Badge 0), or fish with Old Rod later &mdash; <strong>Why:</strong> Incredible stats. Learns Surf. Just fish up a Magikarp early and be patient until it evolves at level 20. One of the best Pokemon in the game.</p><h3>Alakazam / Kadabra</h3><p><strong>Type:</strong> Psychic &mdash; <strong>Where:</strong> Catch Abra (Route 24, Badge 2) &mdash; <strong>Why:</strong> Best special attacker in Gen I. Abra only knows Teleport, so put it to Sleep first. Kadabra is still great even if you cannot trade to evolve it.</p><h3>Snorlax</h3><p><strong>Type:</strong> Normal &mdash; <strong>Where:</strong> Route 12 or 16 (Badge 4, need Poke Flute) &mdash; <strong>Why:</strong> Massive HP tank. Learns a huge variety of moves. Only two available per game, so catch at least one.</p><h3>Jolteon</h3><p><strong>Type:</strong> Electric &mdash; <strong>Where:</strong> Evolve Eevee (Celadon City Mansion, Badge 4) with Thunder Stone &mdash; <strong>Why:</strong> Blazing Speed and strong Sp. Atk. Covers Water and Flying types. Thunderbolt hits hard.</p><h3>Nidoking / Nidoqueen</h3><p><strong>Type:</strong> Poison/Ground &mdash; <strong>Where:</strong> Catch Nidoran (Route 22, Badge 0) &mdash; <strong>Why:</strong> Evolves early with Moon Stone. Learns a massive movepool including Earthquake, Thunderbolt, and Ice Beam. A true jack-of-all-trades.</p><h3>Dodrio</h3><p><strong>Type:</strong> Normal/Flying &mdash; <strong>Where:</strong> Catch Doduo (Route 16-17, Badge 3-4) &mdash; <strong>Why:</strong> Fast and powerful physical attacker. Learns Fly to travel. Great against Erika's Grass gym and Koga's Poison gym.</p><h3>Lapras</h3><p><strong>Type:</strong> Water/Ice &mdash; <strong>Where:</strong> Gift in Silph Co. (Saffron City, Badge 5) &mdash; <strong>Why:</strong> Excellent bulk, learns Surf and Ice Beam. Covers Dragon, Ground, and Flying weaknesses. Only one per game.</p><h2>HeartGold / SoulSilver</h2><h3>Gyarados</h3><p><strong>Type:</strong> Water/Flying &mdash; <strong>Where:</strong> Guaranteed shiny at Lake of Rage (before Badge 7), or fish Magikarp early &mdash; <strong>Why:</strong> Powerhouse stats. Learns Surf, Waterfall, and Ice Fang. A team staple.</p><h3>Ampharos</h3><p><strong>Type:</strong> Electric &mdash; <strong>Where:</strong> Catch Mareep (Route 32, Badge 1) &mdash; <strong>Why:</strong> Solid bulk as an Electric type. Learns Thunder Punch and Signal Beam. Evolves at reasonable levels.</p><h3>Heracross</h3><p><strong>Type:</strong> Bug/Fighting &mdash; <strong>Where:</strong> Headbutt trees (Routes 29, 30, 33) &mdash; <strong>Why:</strong> Enormous Attack stat. Close Combat and Megahorn hit like a truck. Handles Whitney's Miltank easily.</p><h3>Espeon</h3><p><strong>Type:</strong> Psychic &mdash; <strong>Where:</strong> Evolve Eevee (visit Bill in Ecruteak City, then pick up Eevee at his house in Goldenrod) with high friendship during the day &mdash; <strong>Why:</strong> Very fast special attacker. Learns Psychic naturally. Great against Koga, Chuck, and Bruno.</p><h3>Steelix</h3><p><strong>Type:</strong> Steel/Ground &mdash; <strong>Where:</strong> Trade Onix (catch in Union Cave or Dark Cave) &mdash; <strong>Why:</strong> Incredible Defense. Immune to Electric and Poison. Resists most physical attackers. If trading is not available, Onix still walls many threats.</p><h3>Dragonite</h3><p><strong>Type:</strong> Dragon/Flying &mdash; <strong>Where:</strong> Catch Dratini (Dragon's Den or Goldenrod Game Corner) &mdash; <strong>Why:</strong> Late-game powerhouse. Enormous stats across the board. Requires patience &mdash; Dragonair does not evolve until level 55.</p><h3>Quagsire</h3><p><strong>Type:</strong> Water/Ground &mdash; <strong>Where:</strong> Catch Wooper (Route 32 at night, Badge 1) &mdash; <strong>Why:</strong> Only weak to Grass. Immune to Electric. Learns Surf and Earthquake. A simple, effective team member with great type coverage.</p></div>")
